    <div class="reason-grid">
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128293;</span><div class="rc-title">Smoke backing into an elevated hillside home when the fire is first lit</div><div class="rc-desc">Hillside properties can have complex flue draw patterns. A restricted or debris-filled flue causes smoke-back on first use.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128168;</span><div class="rc-title">Damp smell from a fireplace in a property not visited for weeks</div><div class="rc-desc">Peninsula humidity and a closed-up property can result in moisture and mould in the flue. Cleaning and inspection before the season is essential.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#9888;&#65039;</span><div class="rc-title">Bird nest in a peninsula chimney pot</div><div class="rc-desc">Unoccupied or infrequently used properties attract nesting activity in the chimney pot. Annual inspection catches this before it becomes a fire risk.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#127810;</span><div class="rc-title">Annual pre-season clean for a Mount Martha property</div><div class="rc-desc">Whether permanent or weekend use, book in autumn before the cold Bass Strait winter sets in properly.</div></div>
